Spiritual reading is the daily or regular practice of reading Sacred Scripture and other books suitable for nourishing our spiritual life.  Accordingly, it is a key habit to cultivate to attain the central goal of Christian life: a personal encounter with Christ and identification with Him. This explains the importance of reading the New Testament, with the Gospel accounts of Our Lord's life, the Acts and the Apostolic Letters. The daily practice of meditative reading leads to making Christ's life the foundation of one's own existence and is necessarily reflected in one's behavior: "How I wish your bearing and conversation were such that, on seeing or hearing you, people would say: This man reads the life of Jesus Christ" (The Way, no. 2).
